WEBVTT

00:02.586 --> 00:05.803
In Japan, Prime Minister Shinzo Abe...

00:06.289 --> 00:12.595
...said he will declare a state of emergency for Tokyo and six other prefectures as early as Tuesday...

00:12.775 --> 00:18.687
...in the fight against the coronavirus outbreak, but that there will be no hard lockdowns.

00:21.497 --> 00:27.589
In Britain, Prime Minister Boris Johnson, who last week tested positive for the coronavirus,...

00:28.011 --> 00:34.287
...remained hospitalized Monday for additional testing after having a persistent high fever.

00:36.003 --> 00:39.578
In Germany, the government has drawn up a list of steps...

00:39.835 --> 00:46.966
...to help enable a phased return to normal life after its coronavirus lockdown ends on April 19.

00:48.834 --> 00:54.518
In the Ivory Coast, police in Abidjan fired tear gas at protesters...

00:54.872 --> 01:02.135
...after youths set up burning barricades and tried to dismantle a mobile testing center for the coronavirus.

01:02.892 --> 01:09.677
Finally from the US, a tiger at the Bronx Zoo has tested positive for the new coronavirus,...

01:10.053 --> 01:16.900
...in what is believed to be the first known infection in an animal in the United States or a tiger anywhere.

